The paper focuses on measuring and analyzing user behavior in web search, specifically in the domain of journalism for different task types and topics. This falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with the study of searching for information in documents and databases. Additionally, the paper also touches upon natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves analyzing the content of documents and search queries. The study also considers the human-computer interaction aspect (cs.HC) as it looks at subjective measures such as task difficulty and success. Finally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL) as it deals with the search and retrieval of information in a specific domain.
